White House National Security Adviser Jake Sullivan warned on Sunday that Russia would pay a “severe price” if it launched a chemical weapon attack on Ukraine, and said any attack on NATO territory would trigger a full response by the Western alliance. Sullivan told CBS’s “Face the Nation” that the United States and its allies were consulting closely about the increasing threat of a chemical weapons attack, and were communicating directly with Moscow to warn against any such move. “The use of weapons of mass destruction would be a shocking additional line that (Russian President Vladimir) Putin is crossing in terms of his assault on international law and international norms,” Sullivan said. We will not let autocrats and would-be emperors dictate the direction of the world. pic.twitter.com/HH7gJazdmP — Joe Biden (@JoeBiden) March 12, 2022  Russia-Ukraine | Goal is to denazify and de-militarise Ukraine: Russian Embassy in SA